CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "Does This Condition Exist in Other Neighborhoods? Liquor Control Board Should Exercise Better Judgment - One of the overlooked evils in some neighborhoods of Allegheny County is the location of taverns in close proximity to churches, schools and playgrounds. Although such establishments do not operate on Sundays, their presence and the conduct of some patrons prove annoying during the week.... What Does 'License' Mean to Liquor Control Board? 1951 Liquor Laws Governing State Liquor Control Board - Emanuel Baptist Church...next door to this church in Rankin, is a tavern."
TitMainTitle: Street Emanuel Baptist Church, three story brick building with iron balconies, and Esper's Cleaners van parked on street, Rankin
